<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,1221,1567]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,281,1221,1247]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
This species can be identified by its inner spurs of hind tibia much longer than other, exceeding half length of basal tarsal segment (Steinmann, 1965: Fig. 28); pronotum short and broad, constricted in prozona, posterior sulcus placed at anterior third, prozona much shorter than prozona.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,1221,1567]" box="[197,1269,1341,1367]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,314,1341,1367]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Habitats:</emphasis>
It is a species of short grassland and field crops, possible preferably herbivorous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
